#
# This is a sample configuration file for the Lazy CD player.
# Change the settings below to fit to your configuration or preferences.
#
# Below are some alternate CDDB servers:
#
# ADDRESS              PORT          LOCATION
# freedb.freedb.org    888/8880      Random freedb server
# freedb.freedb.de     888/8880      Dortmund, Germany
# at.freedb.org        888/8880      Vienna, Austria
# ca.freedb.org        888/8880      Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada
# de.freedb.org        888/8880      Berlin, Germany
# fr.freedb.org        888/8880      Paris, France
# no.freedb.org        888/8880      Tromso, Norway
# ua.freedb.org        888/8880      Kiev, Ukraine
# uk.freedb.org        888/8880      London, United Kingdom
# us.freedb.org        888/8880      San Jose, California, USA
#
# You can find a more reliable freedb servers by looking at www.freedb.org.
# Send any questions or suggestions to lucasvr@gobolinux.org.
# If you don't want to check for Freedb servers on startup, just use a
# wrong ADDRESS, such as "freedb.freedb.org_"
#

CDDEV=/dev/cdrom                # the CDROM device
AUDIODEV=/dev/dsp               # the AUDIO device, used w/ digital extraction
ADDRESS=freedb.freedb.org       # the CDDB server address
PORT=888                        # the CDDB server port
CDDB_PATH=~/cddb                # path to the local cddb information
REMAINING                       # display remaining time by default instead of elapsed
